{"lemma":"عَوانٍ","slug":"عَوانٍ","root":"ع.#.ن","root_slug":"ع-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَوان","root":"عون","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31110"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَاوَنَ (ʕāwana) (form III)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31110","headword_ar":"عَوَانٌ","root":"Ewn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A beast of the bovine kind, or a cow, (AZ, TA,) or anything, (S, TA,) [i. e.] an animal [of any kind]. (IAar, TA,) or a woman, and a beast, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of middle age,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, IAar, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between such as is advanced in age and the youthful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neither young nor old;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) so in the Kur ii. 63: (S, * TA:) or a cow, and a mare,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has brought, forth after her firstborn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albakoru","text_ar":"البَكْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albikori","text_ar":"البِكْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and a woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has had a hasland;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) in the M,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vay~ibN","text_ar":"ثَيِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwnN","text_ar":"عُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwunN","text_ar":"عُوُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tuEal~amu AlEawaAnu Alximorapa","text_ar":"لَا تُعَلَّمُ العَوَانُ الخِمْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a prov. [expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xmr","text_ar":"خمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".]. (S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN EawaAnN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ عَوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A war in which fighting has occurred once"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is occurring again"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K;) as though they made the first [fighting] to be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bikor","text_ar":"بِكْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or first-horn], (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobapN EawaAnN","text_ar":"ضَرْبَةٌ عَوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blow inflicted by seizing an opportunity when the object is unaware, and requiring to be repeated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarabaAtN EuwnN","text_ar":"ضَرَبَاتٌ عُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., in which the blows of 'Alee are said to have been not of this kind, but such as are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubotakiraAtN","text_ar":"مُبْتَكِرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bikorN","text_ar":"بِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence.]) ―         -b2-  And Land"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watered by rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between two portions of land not so watered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And [the fem. i. e.] with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall"},{"kind":"text","text":"palm-tree: (S, K:) of the dial. of 'Omán, (AHn, S, TA,) or of the dial. of Azd: (TA:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standing alone, apart from others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AZ","TA","S","IAar","Msb","K","AHn"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}